OL,3,CBME women 'twice as likely to be on
OL,4,Czero-hours contracts as white men'
OL,6,FBlack and minority ethnic women are
OL,7,Ftwice as likely to be on zero-hours
OL,8,Fcontracts as white men, research
OL,9,Fsuggests.
OL,11,FThe TUC said its analysis of official
OL,12,Fdata showed that BME workers,
OL,13,Fparticularly women, were more likely
OL,14,Fto be employed on some of the worst
OL,15,Fcontracts.
OL,17,FThe union organisation said the study
OL,18,Fshowed that 5.9% of BME women in work
OL,19,Fare on zero-hours contracts compared
OL,20,Fwith 2.7% of white men.
